        "question type": "Factual Question",
        "question": "Which company did Apple Inc. acquire in an acquisition?",
        "ref": [
            "Apple Inc. conducted an asset acquisition in 2023, acquiring Google Inc."
        ],
        "answer": "Google Inc."
    }},
    {{
        "question type": "Factual Question",
        "question": "In what year was Apple Inc. founded?",
        "ref": [
            ""
        ],
        "answer": "Unable to answer"
    }},
    {{
        "question type": "Multi-hop Reasoning Question",
        "question": "Based on Apple Inc.'s 2023 financial report, how does Apple Inc. support its future investment plans through cost control and capital operation strategies?",
        "ref": [
            "Apple Inc.'s 2023 financial report mentions that through strict cost control strategies, the company reduced unnecessary expenses and optimized resource allocation; through effective capital operation strategies, the company improved capital utilization efficiency and enhanced liquidity.",
            "These measures provided a solid financial foundation for Apple Inc.'s future investment plans."
        ],
        "answer": "Apple Inc. reduced unnecessary expenses through strict cost control strategies, optimized resource allocation; improved capital utilization efficiency through effective capital operation strategies, and enhanced liquidity. These measures provided a financial foundation for future investment plans."
    }},
    {{
        "question type": "Summary Question",
        "question": "Based on Apple Inc.'s 2023 financial report, summarize the financial events that occurred in 2023.",
        "ref": [
            "Apple Inc. conducted large-scale financing activities in 2023, raising substantial funds; completed several important asset acquisitions, expanding its business scope; also underwent debt restructuring, optimizing its financial structure and reducing its debt ratio."
        ],
        "answer": "Apple Inc. conducted large-scale financing activities, raising substantial funds; completed important asset acquisitions, expanding its business scope; underwent debt restructuring, optimizing its financial structure, and reducing its debt ratio."
    }},
    {{
        "question type": "Summary Question",
        "question": "Based on Apple Inc.'s 2023 financial report, summarize its future outlook.",
        "ref": [
            "Apple Inc. plans to continue implementing cost control strategies, further optimizing resource allocation; increase investment in new technologies and product development to maintain market competitiveness; also plans to expand into international markets, exploring new growth opportunities."
        ],
        "answer": "Apple Inc. plans to continue implementing cost control strategies, optimize resource allocation; increase investment in new technologies and product development to maintain market competitiveness; plans to expand into international markets, exploring new growth opportunities."
    }}
]

Incorrect reference recall example:
[
    {{
        "question type": "Factual Question",
        "question": "In which year did the acquisition event of Apple Inc. occur?",
        "ref": [
            "Apple Inc. acquired Google Inc."
        ],
        "answer": "Unable to answer.",
        "Reason": "The reference sentences cannot directly answer the question; they only mention the acquisition event of Apple Inc. Such references are incorrect recalls. The correct approach is not to recall any fragment and output unable to answer."
